title: Sultan Haider wins PP-20 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PMLN) Candidate, Sultan Haider Ali Khan has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-20, Chakwal-I by securing 52,450 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Ali Nasir Khan who bagged 43,250 votes.
The votersâ€™ turnout remained 60.99%.
